list-item.p:
— Teachers should demonstrate evidence of the following competencies/skills through a portfolio, resume, or interview:


understanding of the cognitive and social/emotional characteristics of gifted learners;

development of challenging and rigorous interdisciplinary curriculum appropriate for gifted learners;

development of curriculum that promotes creative, critical, and complex thinking;

delivery of instruction through a variety of methods appropriate for gifted learners;

differentiation of instruction determined by the use of assessment data to meet the academic needs, interests, and learning styles of gifted students;

ability to address a relevant, real-world problem through authentic tasks such as service learning;

development of multiple assessments to monitor students’ growth;

capacity to communicate with students, school staff, families, and community members, and collaborate with them in support of students;

evidence of teacher leadership and participation on school reform, improvement, curriculum teams, or other related duties; and

passion for lifelong learning.
